The shepheard and the king, and of Gillian the shepheards vvife with her churlish answers: being full of mirth and merry pastime. To the tune of Flying fane [sic].
1 sheet ([1] p.) : ill. (woodcuts)
s.n., [London : ca. 1635]
Verse - "An older time there was fo yore,". Imprint from STC. In two parts, printed side by side. In this edition, last line of 1st stanza has: 'Jouiall'. Reproduction of original in the Pepysian Library, Magdalene College, Cambridge, England.
